OL,4,Cfridge jailed
OL,6,FThe remains of Mr O'Sullivan had been
OL,7,Fwrapped in a tarpaulin and a duvet and
OL,8,Fpartially placed in a fridge in the
OL,9,Fliving room. Sadly he had been dead
OL,10,Ffor some time.
OL,12,FDuring sentencing, the court heard
OL,13,Fthat the defendant claimed he did not
OL,14,Falert the authorities because he
OL,15,Fwanted to protect his father's dignity
OL,16,Fand privacy.
OL,18,FHe claimed he placed him in the fridge
OL,19,Fbecause that is what they would have
OL,20,Fdone at Altnagelivin Hospital.
